    "updated_at": "2023-07-06T09:29:43Z",
    "body": "Sorry for the delay in replying but I think I know what is going on here. The problem is not related to the kubernetes module but that is just the first module so the delay shows up. What is happening is starship is scanning the current directory to build an internal representation of what it contains, so each module doesn't have to redo the same work, it is this scan that is slow when you have dns issues as it trys to check your `doc` dir and from you example it looks like the kubernetes module is just the first module to run so it includes the time for the scan. ",
